The paper deals with the problem of obfuscating sensitive information while preserving utility, which is a common topic in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed approach is based on machine learning, specifically on the GANs paradigm, which is a popular topic in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments are performed on synthetic and real data, which suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of databases (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the tradeoff between privacy and utility, which is a common topic in the field of social and information networks (cs.SI).
